My last meal in Vegas was to be at the Wynn Buffet. I know everyone has their ideas of who has the best buffet, and for the money Wynn was pretty good. 

I started off with one plate of light and healthy food;
http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/2weQS-RnoOBhb1KsHKyoSQ?select=XAIe2EouM1VRMsZOZv_TBw

Then a second plate of light and healthy food;
http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/2weQS-RnoOBhb1KsHKyoSQ?select=7Cyk37tWGZpwYpucogEFKw

Then we wanted to try half of all the desserts;
http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/2weQS-RnoOBhb1KsHKyoSQ?select=fG5mYm_KpSyQVUJHH_-fNg

Then another batch of the remaining desserts;
http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/2weQS-RnoOBhb1KsHKyoSQ?select=SFFPumnxHer-hoYQqeMRSw

Then the last few, yet to be tasted, desserts;
http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/2weQS-RnoOBhb1KsHKyoSQ?select=OxZmAkenCPealApavCmlSg

To say I left full and jacked up on sugar would be an understatement. But I did leave feeling as though I did a good job eating in Vegas.
